[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two men killed in HGVs collision on A90 north of Balmedie

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two HGV drivers have died in a collision on the A90 in Aberdeenshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident happened on the Foveran to Balmedie stretch near Hatterseat at about 13:20.
Police Scotland said diversions were in place and urged motorists to avoid the area for the remainder of the evening.
The female driver of a car also involved was taken to Aberdeen Royal Infirmary for treatment for minor injuries.
A collision investigation has been launched.
Sgt Steve Manson said: "We would appeal for anyone who was in the area around the time of this collision and saw what happened to contact us."
